<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="350" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,412,871]" pageId="1" pageNumber="350">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,412,438]" pageId="1" pageNumber="350">Description.</emphasis>
Dorsum yellow, reddish, white or brown, patterned with red, orange or brown. Head narrower than pronotum. Crown fore margin weakly produced. Vertex midline pale, and usually with pair of dark or light preapical spots. Anteclypeus narrow and pale, concolorous with rest of face or dark. Pronotum pale, scutellum with dark lateral triangles. Forewings with or without oblique vittae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,412,871]" pageId="1" pageNumber="350">Male abdominal apodemes small, narrow, extended dorsomesad, or large, broad, reaching or exceeding the posterior margin of 3rd sternite.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,412,871]" pageId="1" pageNumber="350">Pygofer lobe rounded, microtrichia well developed, without fine setae in dorsal membrane. Pygofer dorsal appendage movably articulated, ventral appendage absent. Subgenital plate with 2-4 basal macrosetae on outer margin; marginal subbasal setae peglike, forming continuous row. Style with preapical lobe prominent, apex truncate and expanded or with 3 points. Aedeagal shaft usually symmetrical, with paired or unpaired processes, with preatrium shorter than shaft or about as long as shaft. Connective with lateral arms long, stem absent or very short, and median anterior lobe absent.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
